  calories: 874 kcal
  fat: 33 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 113 g
  protein: 43 g
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/pasta-al-forno-with-roasted-aubergine-and-mozzarella-7-56a8f5f94dab718f088b4567
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
---

Pre-heat your #oven to 220 degrees. Chop the very top and bottom from the @aubergine{1} and then cut it in half lengthways. Slice each half lengthways into five pieces then chop it into 2cm cubes. Coat in @olive oil{1%tbsp}, a @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} and roast on a #baking tray{} for ~{20%minutes}.

Peel and finely chop @onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and finely chopped). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{4}. Chop up the @black olives{1} (removing any stones).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #nonstick frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Cook the onion and garlic for around ~{5%minutes}, or until soft.

> You only want to soften the ingredients, not brown them off.

Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}, for your pasta. Add the @chopped tomatoes{1}, @dried oregano{1/2} and olives to the onion mixture. Turn the heat to low and slowly cook the sauce until the aubergine is cooked (in the oven).

> Once the excess water in the tomatoes has gone and the sauce has thickened, it is ready.

Cook the @wheat penne pasta{200%g} in the boiling water for about ~{10%minutes} or until 'al dente'.

> Pasta is 'al dente' when it is cooked through but has a hint of firmness in the middle.

Once the aubergine is soft and a little crispy around the edges mix it into the tomato sauce.

Drain the pasta and mix it thoroughly into the sauce. Tear the @basil{1/2}(torn into small pieces) and @mozzarella{1}(torn into small pieces) and stir through the pasta. Pour the pasta into an #ovenproof dish{}.

Scatter the grated cheddar cheese across the top and put the dish in the hot oven. Cook for around ~{10-15%minutes} or until the cheddar is browned off and crispy.

Drizzle @olive oil{1%tsp} and the @balsamic vinegar{1} over the @wild rocket{1}. Sprinkle on a @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} and the @pine nuts{1}. Serve a healthy spoonful of your pasta with the rocket salad on the side.

> You can brown the pine nuts off by putting them in the oven for 5 mins.